{
  "texts": [
    "Being informed and knowledgeable about the limitations and risks of AI technologies ensures that patients can weigh these factors against potential benefits when consenting to AI use in their treatment.",
    "TransparencyTransparency in AI systems is important not only for patients but also for physicians, who serve as the primary receivers and communicators of AI-driven medical information.",
    "A clear understanding of how AI-based applications work, particularly how decision-making processes are performed, is required for physicians to effectively communicate with their patients [48].",
    "Such informed communication is a fundamental aspect of the informed consent process, fostering a deeper understanding and trust within the physician-patient relationship [49].",
    "When patients receive comprehensive and transparent information from their trusted health care providers, they enhance their engagement and participation in decision-making."
  ]
}